translate ru strings:

    old "Nearly a week had passed since Sarah had officially signed on to work for captain Belmont."
    new "Nearly a week had passed since Sarah had officially signed on to work for captain Belmont."

    old "The first lesson that Sarah had come to learn about sailing was that for as often as it could be exciting, so too could it be boring."
    new "The first lesson that Sarah had come to learn about sailing was that for as often as it could be exciting, so too could it be boring."

    old "The ship had remained docked in Rahayal ever since they arrived."
    new "The ship had remained docked in Rahayal ever since they arrived."

    old "On the odd day, Sarah would be instructed to load or unload crates from and to the ship."
    new "On the odd day, Sarah would be instructed to load or unload crates from and to the ship."

    old "Other than that, her days were filled with maintaining the ship."
    new "Other than that, her days were filled with maintaining the ship."

    old "The soot of the city's industry clogged the air, and with it, slowly dirtied most every part of the ship."
    new "The soot of the city's industry clogged the air, and with it, slowly dirtied most every part of the ship."

    old "Scrubbing the deck was far from the only work. She washed the captain's clothes, his sheets and his dishes."
    new "Scrubbing the deck was far from the only work. She washed the captain's clothes, his sheets and his dishes."

    old "More than once he'd drag her into his bed, and after finishing, leave her to clean the mess."
    new "More than once he'd drag her into his bed, and after finishing, leave her to clean the mess."

    old "It wasn't fair, but then again, Sarah rationalized, Belmont had never pretended that their arrangement would be fair."
    new "It wasn't fair, but then again, Sarah rationalized, Belmont had never pretended that their arrangement would be fair."

    old "There was a hierarchy on this ship, and she most definitely sat at the bottom."
    new "There was a hierarchy on this ship, and she most definitely sat at the bottom."

    old "Still, Sarah managed."
    new "Still, Sarah managed."

    old "The labour had a way of clearing her mind."
    new "The labour had a way of clearing her mind."

    old "Despite everything, she had finally been sleeping easy. No doubt, she thought, the work helped with that as well."
    new "Despite everything, she had finally been sleeping easy. No doubt, she thought, the work helped with that as well."

    old "Her muscles were sore as she worked the upper deck, pushing and pulling the wet mop across the wooden surface of the ship."
    new "Her muscles were sore as she worked the upper deck, pushing and pulling the wet mop across the wooden surface of the ship."

    old "The pain in her muscles made her happy. Happy at being useful."
    new "The pain in her muscles made her happy. Happy at being useful."

    old "Off the side of the ship, Sarah could spot the bustling city life of Rahayal."
    new "Off the side of the ship, Sarah could spot the bustling city life of Rahayal."

    old "Captain Belmont was off the ship, doing god knows what during the day, so Sarah could occasionally afford to slack and watch the city life."
    new "Captain Belmont was off the ship, doing god knows what during the day, so Sarah could occasionally afford to slack and watch the city life."

    old "It was a bit like an ant colony, she'd come to realize."
    new "It was a bit like an ant colony, she'd come to realize."

    old "Initially, it all seemed like a crawling chaos, just people moving round and about in every direction."
    new "Initially, it all seemed like a crawling chaos, just people moving round and about in every direction."

    old "But the more she studied the city and its people, the more she came to understand that behind the chaos was in fact quite an organized dance."
    new "But the more she studied the city and its people, the more she came to understand that behind the chaos was in fact quite an organized dance."

    old "Merchants meeting with officials, cargo men bringing up the carts, sailors loading and unloading cargo."
    new "Merchants meeting with officials, cargo men bringing up the carts, sailors loading and unloading cargo."

    old "Each person played a part in a larger whole that was unknown to them."
    new "Each person played a part in a larger whole that was unknown to them."

    old "Among the throng of people, there was the occasional rare person of means. Gentleman and ladies whose dress alone signalled that they stood apart from the others."
    new "Among the throng of people, there was the occasional rare person of means. Gentleman and ladies whose dress alone signalled that they stood apart from the others."

    old "Sarah knew enough about Rahayal that there were no noble houses. At least, not in the way they existed in Rosanna or the other union countries."
    new "Sarah knew enough about Rahayal that there were no noble houses. At least, not in the way they existed in Rosanna or the other union countries."

    old "In Rahayal, same as the rest of the Mythran empire, there were only three classes of people. Citizens, slaves and the Noster."
    new "In Rahayal, same as the rest of the Mythran empire, there were only three classes of people. Citizens, slaves and the Noster."

    old "The citizens, despite their common title, made up only a small part of the empire's population, around ten percent."
    new "The citizens, despite their common title, made up only a small part of the empire's population, around ten percent."

    old "The other ninety percent was comprised of slaves, but even here the Mythran empire was different."
    new "The other ninety percent was comprised of slaves, but even here the Mythran empire was different."

    old "Slaves in Mythra, unlike most other places that still practiced slavery, practiced one where the slaves occupied all manner of vocations."
    new "Slaves in Mythra, unlike most other places that still practiced slavery, practiced one where the slaves occupied all manner of vocations."

    old "There were slave soldiers, craftsmen, sailors. There were even slave generals and slave diplomats."
    new "There were slave soldiers, craftsmen, sailors. There were even slave generals and slave diplomats."

    old "As such, a slave could very well be more powerful or influential than a citizen."
    new "As such, a slave could very well be more powerful or influential than a citizen."

    old "The real difference was that the slave class served as a functional extention of the Noster, the true rulers of Mythra."
    new "The real difference was that the slave class served as a functional extention of the Noster, the true rulers of Mythra."

    old "The slave class simply did as instructed. From birth, one would be told what their role would be, and they would be trained from youth to perform their inevitable function."
    new "The slave class simply did as instructed. From birth, one would be told what their role would be, and they would be trained from youth to perform their inevitable function."

    old "The citizens, on the other hand, were given a larger degree of freedom to shape their own lives."
    new "The citizens, on the other hand, were given a larger degree of freedom to shape their own lives."

    old "A citizen could succeed on his own merit, but unlike a slave, he could also fall into poverty."
    new "A citizen could succeed on his own merit, but unlike a slave, he could also fall into poverty."

    old "Growing up in Castle Reinmeer, Sarah had read more books than she could count on all the nations of the world."
    new "Growing up in Castle Reinmeer, Sarah had read more books than she could count on all the nations of the world."

    old "In her mind, she had given them shape and colour, dreamt of what their world might be like."
    new "In her mind, she had given them shape and colour, dreamt of what their world might be like."

    old "Standing here in person, she realized just how short her imagination fell from the real thing."
    new "Standing here in person, she realized just how short her imagination fell from the real thing."

    old "Never could she have dreamt up the intricate details, sounds and smells of this place. Reading about it, she came to understand, meant nothing compared to seeing it."
    new "Never could she have dreamt up the intricate details, sounds and smells of this place. Reading about it, she came to understand, meant nothing compared to seeing it."

    old "Off to the far side of the dock, Sarah watched a rich lady yell and scold her servant."
    new "Off to the far side of the dock, Sarah watched a rich lady yell and scold her servant."

    old "Was I like that?"
    new "Was I like that?"

    old "Sarah spoke aloud, though only she could hear."
    new "Sarah spoke aloud, though only she could hear."

    old "She had always thought the world was a mostly fair place, where everyone got what they deserved."
    new "She had always thought the world was a mostly fair place, where everyone got what they deserved."

    old "Only now, having fallen so far down the ladder, Sarah could see there was very little about this world that was fair."
    new "Only now, having fallen so far down the ladder, Sarah could see there was very little about this world that was fair."

    old "The rich lady was scolding the servant girl, and yet Sarah thought, flip a coin and switch their births, and the servant girl would be scolding the lady."
    new "The rich lady was scolding the servant girl, and yet Sarah thought, flip a coin and switch their births, and the servant girl would be scolding the lady."

    old "All just playing their part in a system. A system that Sarah was only now beginning to experience from the inside."
    new "All just playing their part in a system. A system that Sarah was only now beginning to experience from the inside."

    old "She grabbed her mop and got back to work."
    new "She grabbed her mop and got back to work."

    old "The sun had begun to set and Sarah was leaning across the side of the ship."
    new "The sun had begun to set and Sarah was leaning across the side of the ship."

    old "She closed her eyes and let the setting sun warm her face."
    new "She closed her eyes and let the setting sun warm her face."

    old "She almost dared to be happy."
    new "She almost dared to be happy."

    old "Hey! Blondie, don't be sleepin on the job!"
    new "Hey! Blondie, don't be sleepin on the job!"

    old "Sarah was startled."
    new "Sarah was startled."

    old "She opened her eyes and saw captain Belmont already walking up the plank towards the ship."
    new "She opened her eyes and saw captain Belmont already walking up the plank towards the ship."

    old "I-I-I'm sorry captain Belmont! Apologies!"
    new "I-I-I'm sorry captain Belmont! Apologies!"

    old "To hell with your apologies, blondie. Best you hope I don't find any dirt nowhere on my ship or you can scrub into the night."
    new "To hell with your apologies, blondie. Best you hope I don't find any dirt nowhere on my ship or you can scrub into the night."

    old "No, captain Belmont! I promise, sir, the ship is spotless!"
    new "No, captain Belmont! I promise, sir, the ship is spotless!"

    old "She heard him grunt some words, perhaps only half believing her."
    new "She heard him grunt some words, perhaps only half believing her."

    old "This here is Nickolas, but you can just call him Nick."
    new "This here is Nickolas, but you can just call him Nick."

    old "Belmont gestured behind him."
    new "Belmont gestured behind him."

    old "Only now did Sarah realized someone else had boarded the ship along captain Belmont."
    new "Only now did Sarah realized someone else had boarded the ship along captain Belmont."

    old "He had broad shoulders, waving blonde hair that seemed almost gold and a smile that drowned out everything else in the world."
    new "He had broad shoulders, waving blonde hair that seemed almost gold and a smile that drowned out everything else in the world."

    old "The husband of her dreams had somehow stepped into the real world."
    new "The husband of her dreams had somehow stepped into the real world."

    old "Hey, I'm Nick."
    new "Hey, I'm Nick."

    old "He extended his hand to her."
    new "He extended his hand to her."

    old "Unthinking, Sarah grabbed it and shook his hand."
    new "Unthinking, Sarah grabbed it and shook his hand."

    old "As she was shaking his hand, she could see his broad, muscular arms, pressing against his shirt."
    new "As she was shaking his hand, she could see his broad, muscular arms, pressing against his shirt."

    old "Nice to meet you, Sarah."
    new "Nice to meet you, Sarah."

    old "Yeah...uhm, nice to meet you too."
    new "Yeah...uhm, nice to meet you too."

    old "Belmont walked in between them."
    new "Belmont walked in between them."

    old "Enough of this, come along boy. You need to sign some documents to make this official."
    new "Enough of this, come along boy. You need to sign some documents to make this official."

    old "Yes, captain."
    new "Yes, captain."

    old "Sarah watched Belmont walk down into the bowels of the ship, and Nick following him."
    new "Sarah watched Belmont walk down into the bowels of the ship, and Nick following him."

    old "Just before he dissapeared below deck, he gave her a small wave and a smile."
    new "Just before he dissapeared below deck, he gave her a small wave and a smile."

    old "Sarah returned him the same before she even realized."
    new "Sarah returned him the same before she even realized."

    old "The deck was empty again."
    new "The deck was empty again."

    old "Sarah stared at the door that lead below deck for a moment longer. It was almost like a shade of him lingered there."
    new "Sarah stared at the door that lead below deck for a moment longer. It was almost like a shade of him lingered there."

    old "She began to laugh to herself."
    new "She began to laugh to herself."

    old "Get it together, Sarah."
    new "Get it together, Sarah."

    old "Was this her life becoming somewhat normal again, she thought?"
    new "Was this her life becoming somewhat normal again, she thought?"

    old "Back to thinking about silly, unimportant things. Stupid crushes."
    new "Back to thinking about silly, unimportant things. Stupid crushes."

    old "With a spring in her step, Sarah went back to her duties."
    new "With a spring in her step, Sarah went back to her duties."

    old "It was almost an hour later when the two finally emerged from below deck."
    new "It was almost an hour later when the two finally emerged from below deck."

    old "Blondie, get over here."
    new "Blondie, get over here."

    old "Sarah dropped what she was doing and came over."
    new "Sarah dropped what she was doing and came over."

    old "She tousled her hair and gave Nick a quick smile."
    new "She tousled her hair and gave Nick a quick smile."

    old "Yes, captain?"
    new "Yes, captain?"

    old "Nick over here is gonna be joining our crew."
    new "Nick over here is gonna be joining our crew."

    old "Sarah was surprised."
    new "Sarah was surprised."

    old "I thought I was your deck hand, captain?"
    new "I thought I was your deck hand, captain?"

    old "You are, you'll both be."
    new "You are, you'll both be."

    old "But I just took on a contract for delivering a large haul of coal to the city of Northam, and that's not the kinda trip for an inexperienced sailor."
    new "But I just took on a contract for delivering a large haul of coal to the city of Northam, and that's not the kinda trip for an inexperienced sailor."

    old "Belmont padded Nick on the back."
    new "Belmont padded Nick on the back."

    old "Nick here has a couple a years of experience workin as a deck hand."
    new "Nick here has a couple a years of experience workin as a deck hand."

    old "You can try and learn a thing or two from him blondie."
    new "You can try and learn a thing or two from him blondie."

    old "Yes captain!"
    new "Yes captain!"

    old "Sarah looked at Nick's deep blue eyes. Blue like sapphires."
    new "Sarah looked at Nick's deep blue eyes. Blue like sapphires."

    old "I look forward to learn from you, Nick."
    new "I look forward to learn from you, Nick."

    old "That's alright. I'm sure you're a fast learner, the captain speaks highly of you."
    new "That's alright. I'm sure you're a fast learner, the captain speaks highly of you."

    old "Sarah smiled a wide grin."
    new "Sarah smiled a wide grin."

    old "Does he?"
    new "Does he?"

    old "Don't go gettin an attitude now blondie."
    new "Don't go gettin an attitude now blondie."

    old "Anyway, the plan is to set out in two days. The trip is nearly two weeks and we're gonna be passin some rough waters."
    new "Anyway, the plan is to set out in two days. The trip is nearly two weeks and we're gonna be passin some rough waters."

    old "I need to get the paperwork sorted and meet with some suppliers to make sure we can make the trip."
    new "I need to get the paperwork sorted and meet with some suppliers to make sure we can make the trip."

    old "You teach her the ropes, alright boy?"
    new "You teach her the ropes, alright boy?"

    old "Nick nodded."
    new "Nick nodded."

    old "Yes captain."
    new "Yes captain."

    old "Sarah watched as captain Belmont departed the ship, heading towards the marketplace."
    new "Sarah watched as captain Belmont departed the ship, heading towards the marketplace."

    old "She turned back to Nick."
    new "She turned back to Nick."

    old "With only themselves left on the ship, and no longer needing to hide her eyes from the captain, Sarah could properly look at Nick for the first time."
    new "With only themselves left on the ship, and no longer needing to hide her eyes from the captain, Sarah could properly look at Nick for the first time."

    old "Gods, he was beautiful."
    new "Gods, he was beautiful."

    old "In addition to being naturally tall, towering over Sarah by at least a head, he was also strong."
    new "In addition to being naturally tall, towering over Sarah by at least a head, he was also strong."

    old "His body was muscular in a way that betrayed his hard life of manual labor."
    new "His body was muscular in a way that betrayed his hard life of manual labor."

    old "Still, if this was what being a deck hand did to your body, perhaps all men ought to be deck hands, she concluded."
    new "Still, if this was what being a deck hand did to your body, perhaps all men ought to be deck hands, she concluded."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah snapped back to the present."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah snapped back to the present."

    old "What? I-no I didn't, I mean, I wasn't staring."
    new "What? I-no I didn't, I mean, I wasn't staring."

    old "Daydreaming then? That's a dangerous game to play on a ship."
    new "Daydreaming then? That's a dangerous game to play on a ship."

    old "Sarah laughed, excessively she realized. Get it together, she reminded herself."
    new "Sarah laughed, excessively she realized. Get it together, she reminded herself."

    old "Sorry, I'm just a bit nervous. I don't know too much about sailing yet, so I'm just happy to learn."
    new "Sorry, I'm just a bit nervous. I don't know too much about sailing yet, so I'm just happy to learn."

    old "Has the captain taught you anything?"
    new "Has the captain taught you anything?"

    old "A bit, here and there."
    new "A bit, here and there."

    old "The problem is that he's very busy, so whenever he starts to explain something, he just realizes its faster if he does it himself."
    new "The problem is that he's very busy, so whenever he starts to explain something, he just realizes its faster if he does it himself."

    old "But then I think I'll never learn if I don't get a chance."
    new "But then I think I'll never learn if I don't get a chance."

    old "So I'm glad that you can maybe walk me through the steps a bit slower, ya know?"
    new "So I'm glad that you can maybe walk me through the steps a bit slower, ya know?"

    old "Of course. Trust me, by the end of this trip, you'll know all the ropes."
    new "Of course. Trust me, by the end of this trip, you'll know all the ropes."

    old "Sarah learned over the course of that first day that Nick was a man of his words."
    new "Sarah learned over the course of that first day that Nick was a man of his words."

    old "He walked her through all the steps for preparing a ship for departure. Taking his time, allowing her to try, giving corrections."
    new "He walked her through all the steps for preparing a ship for departure. Taking his time, allowing her to try, giving corrections."

    old "Sarah studied his every move and listened intently when he spoke."
    new "Sarah studied his every move and listened intently when he spoke."

    old "It helped that he was easy to look at and easy to listen to."
    new "It helped that he was easy to look at and easy to listen to."

    old "Before Sarah fully realized, the day neared its end."
    new "Before Sarah fully realized, the day neared its end."

    old "They were sitting off to the side of the ship, looking out over the dock."
    new "They were sitting off to the side of the ship, looking out over the dock."

    old "Thank you, Nick. I think I've learned more today than I did in all the weeks before."
    new "Thank you, Nick. I think I've learned more today than I did in all the weeks before."

    old "No need to thank me. You're probably the best student I ever had."
    new "No need to thank me. You're probably the best student I ever had."

    old "He smiled in that carefree easygoing way that Sarah had started to love despite only knowing him for less than a day."
    new "He smiled in that carefree easygoing way that Sarah had started to love despite only knowing him for less than a day."

    old "She couldn't help but smile back at him."
    new "She couldn't help but smile back at him."

    old "So, how did you end up working as a deck hand? You don't strike me as the type."
    new "So, how did you end up working as a deck hand? You don't strike me as the type."

    old "Ooh, I guess I never really planned for it."
    new "Ooh, I guess I never really planned for it."

    old "But I was living in Lethram, and things weren't really working out for me, so I needed a change."
    new "But I was living in Lethram, and things weren't really working out for me, so I needed a change."

    old "And I realized I love the ocean, so I figured, why not keep at it."
    new "And I realized I love the ocean, so I figured, why not keep at it."

    old "Yeah, I can relate to that."
    new "Yeah, I can relate to that."

    old "I was born in Lethram, but I never really felt like I had a home either. I just kinda drift from port to port, work when I can."
    new "I was born in Lethram, but I never really felt like I had a home either. I just kinda drift from port to port, work when I can."

    old "It's easy enough, but I'm not really sure where I'm going yet."
    new "It's easy enough, but I'm not really sure where I'm going yet."

    old "Yeah, that sounds familiar too."
    new "Yeah, that sounds familiar too."

    old "So why did you decide to sign on with captain Belmont?"
    new "So why did you decide to sign on with captain Belmont?"

    old "Nick shrugged."
    new "Nick shrugged."

    old "He pays well. Not much more too it than that."
    new "He pays well. Not much more too it than that."

    old "Sarah and Nick continued their conversation."
    new "Sarah and Nick continued their conversation."

    old "Sarah found herself surprised at just how easy it was to talk to him."
    new "Sarah found herself surprised at just how easy it was to talk to him."

    old "Maybe it had been a while since she'd actually met someone who was just a genuinely nice person."
    new "Maybe it had been a while since she'd actually met someone who was just a genuinely nice person."

    old "Time flew until eventually their conversation was interrupted."
    new "Time flew until eventually their conversation was interrupted."

    old "Do I pay you two to blabber about or to work my ship?"
    new "Do I pay you two to blabber about or to work my ship?"

    old "The plank creaked as captain Belmont made his way back onto the ship."
    new "The plank creaked as captain Belmont made his way back onto the ship."

    old "Sarah and Nick leapt to their feet."
    new "Sarah and Nick leapt to their feet."

    old "Sorry captain!"
    new "Sorry captain!"

    old "Belmont waved his hands."
    new "Belmont waved his hands."

    old "Whatever. Have you prepped the sail rigs?"
    new "Whatever. Have you prepped the sail rigs?"

    old "Yes, captain. I showed Sarah how to do it as well."
    new "Yes, captain. I showed Sarah how to do it as well."

    old "I've settled up with a supplier, we should be getting food and other stocking tomorrow."
    new "I've settled up with a supplier, we should be getting food and other stocking tomorrow."

    old "Have you gotten settled in yet below deck?"
    new "Have you gotten settled in yet below deck?"

    old "Nick shook his head."
    new "Nick shook his head."

    old "No, not yet captain."
    new "No, not yet captain."

    old "Well, you're gonna have to get up early tomorrow. Both of you."
    new "Well, you're gonna have to get up early tomorrow. Both of you."

    old "Blondie, go and help him get set up in the bunks at the back of the ship."
    new "Blondie, go and help him get set up in the bunks at the back of the ship."

    old "Sarah turned to Nick."
    new "Sarah turned to Nick."

    old "Together, they dissapeared below deck."
    new "Together, they dissapeared below deck."

    old "Arriving below deck, it had already turned dark."
    new "Arriving below deck, it had already turned dark."

    old "Sarah guided Nick to the back of the ship where the bunks were."
    new "Sarah guided Nick to the back of the ship where the bunks were."

    old "You can get settled here."
    new "You can get settled here."

    old "There are some covers here, we keep the linnens in that chest over there."
    new "There are some covers here, we keep the linnens in that chest over there."

    old "I think there should still be a fresh pillow, but just let me know if it's not, I can get you another."
    new "I think there should still be a fresh pillow, but just let me know if it's not, I can get you another."

    old "Nick smiled at her as he slapped the pillow."
    new "Nick smiled at her as he slapped the pillow."

    old "Nah. This seems fine."
    new "Nah. This seems fine."

    old "I'm used to sleeping on floors, so this is already an upgrade."
    new "I'm used to sleeping on floors, so this is already an upgrade."

    old "Nick scanned the room from end to end."
    new "Nick scanned the room from end to end."

    old "Where do you sleep?"
    new "Where do you sleep?"

    old "Sarah felt her throat seize up at his question."
    new "Sarah felt her throat seize up at his question."

    old "I don't sleep here..."
    new "I don't sleep here..."

    old "Nick looked at her, that same casual attitude that he always seemed to have."
    new "Nick looked at her, that same casual attitude that he always seemed to have."

    old "Ooh, your room is somewhere else?"
    new "Ooh, your room is somewhere else?"

    old "Sarah didn't know what to say, so she simply spoke the truth."
    new "Sarah didn't know what to say, so she simply spoke the truth."

    old "I sleep in the captain's cabin."
    new "I sleep in the captain's cabin."

    old "She watched Nick's brow furrow."
    new "She watched Nick's brow furrow."

    old "In his cabin?"
    new "In his cabin?"

    old "Sarah felt her voice go soft."
    new "Sarah felt her voice go soft."

    old "She had loved today. Meeting someone like Nick had made her believe that her life wouldn't be an endless tragedy."
    new "She had loved today. Meeting someone like Nick had made her believe that her life wouldn't be an endless tragedy."

    old "But now she had to confess this fact to him."
    new "But now she had to confess this fact to him."

    old "I sleep in his cabin."
    new "I sleep in his cabin."

    old "Sarah kept her eyes to the floor."
    new "Sarah kept her eyes to the floor."

    old "Her relationship with the captain had been one she had come around to accepting. Accepting to herself."
    new "Her relationship with the captain had been one she had come around to accepting. Accepting to herself."

    old "And to some degree, it had been easy for her, because whatever had existed between her and Belmont had been a secret."
    new "And to some degree, it had been easy for her, because whatever had existed between her and Belmont had been a secret."

    old "Whatever shame she carried from it had always been private, between herself and the captain."
    new "Whatever shame she carried from it had always been private, between herself and the captain."

    old "Now he knew. How would he look at her? Would he think she was disgusting? Sarah thought over herself that she was."
    new "Now he knew. How would he look at her? Would he think she was disgusting? Sarah thought over herself that she was."

    old "Ooh. I didn't know you and he were...I see."
    new "Ooh. I didn't know you and he were...I see."

    old "Sarah looked up, tears in her eyes and shook her head."
    new "Sarah looked up, tears in her eyes and shook her head."

    old "No, it's not...it's not like that."
    new "No, it's not...it's not like that."

    old "It's not, I mean, it's not love. I don't love him."
    new "It's not, I mean, it's not love. I don't love him."

    old "To her own surprise, she didn't see revulsion in his face. Only sympathy."
    new "To her own surprise, she didn't see revulsion in his face. Only sympathy."

    old "Fuck. Why did he have to be so kind."
    new "Fuck. Why did he have to be so kind."

    old "Well, I think I understand. We all have to do things sometimes. To survive."
    new "Well, I think I understand. We all have to do things sometimes. To survive."

    old "He understood. He actually understood her."
